Date: 29 Mar 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong Department of Health 29 Mar 2003 [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>


Figures on atypical pneumonia
------------------
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:

As at 1 PM 29 Mar 2003, a total of 470 people with pneumonia symptoms have
been admitted to public hospitals. The 45 additional patients reported
today include 3 healthcare workers and 22 patients from Amoy Gardens. The
remaining 23 were new patients and contacts of patients with atypical
pneumonia.

The DH has visited Amoy Gardens last night and performed screening of its
residents to ensure their health. A medical surveillance post has been set
up to address health concerns of the residents. Investigations including a
detailed questionnaire study of the cases are being performed.

As at today, 43 patients have been discharged from hospitals. A total of 53
patients are receiving treatment in the intensive care unit.

An 85-year-old male patient with history of cardiac disease died in Prince
of Wales Hospital this morning, bringing to 12 the total number of patients
died with atypical pneumonia.

The breakdown of figures is as follows:

Nature Total Admission (The numbers in bracket are those with pneumonia
symptoms)

Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students 156 (156)
24 of the patients were discharged
Patients, family members & visitors 314 (314)
19 of the patients were discharged

Total admission 470 (470)
43 were discharged

